//Why we need appsettings.json file in ASP.NET Core?

// the appsettings.json file is used to strore configuration settings  e.g connnectionstring, jwt settings, azure blob, twillo, sendgrid, etc. It is a common practice to use appsettings.json file to store configuration settings in ASP.NET Core applications because it provides a centralized location for all configuration settings and allows for easy management and maintenance of these settings. Additionally, the appsettings.json file can be easily modified without the need to recompile the application, making it a convenient way to manage configuration settings in a production environment.
